<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
2. 
<taxonomicName LSID="70440A9D-96FF-5208-A2EE-139008B01E40" authority="Griff., Itin. Pl. Khasyah Mts. 40, No. 652. (1848)" authorityName="Griff., Itin. Pl. Khasyah Mts. 40, No. 652. (1848)" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="Camellia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Camellia symplocifolia" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="symplocifolia">Camellia symplocifolia Griff., Itin. Pl. Khasyah Mts. 40, No. 652. (1848)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="lectotype">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Lectotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
(designated here): India. Khasya Hills, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">W. Griffith s.n.</emphasis>
(TCD0018254!; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Lectotype of Camellia symplocifolia Griff. (Griffith s. n., TCD 0018254). The red arrow indicates one position of the androecium and gynoecium. Image scanned by Ms J. Stone (TCD) and adapted by D. W. Zhao." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.84699.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702560" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.70351" author="Griffith, W" journalOrPublisher="Bellamy, Calcutta" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B9" refString="Griffith, W, 1848. Itinerary Notes of Plants Collected in the Khasyah and Bootan Mountains, 1837-38, in Affghanisthan and Neighbouring Countries, 1839 to 1841. Arranged by J. M'Clelland. Printed by Mr. J.F. Bellamy, Calcutta, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.70351" title="Itinerary Notes of Plants Collected in the Khasyah and Bootan Mountains, 1837 - 38, in Affghanisthan and Neighbouring Countries, 1839 to 1841. Arranged by J. M'Clelland. Printed by Mr. J. F." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.70351" year="1848">Griffith (1848)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. symplocifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="symplocifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">C. symplocifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under his catalogue number 652 and stated that the original material was collected at Churra, Khasyah. Though &quot;Icon no. 31&quot; was cited in the protologue and this citation directs to a drawing, fig. 2 of plate DCIV (&quot; 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. simplicifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="simplicifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">C. simplicifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;) in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Icones Plantarum Asiaticarum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.63664" author="Griffith, W" journalOrPublisher="Bellamy, Calcutta" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B10" refString="Griffith, W, 1854. Icones Plantarum Asiaticarum. Part IV, Diccotyledonous Plants. Arranged by J. M'Clelland. Printed by A.B. Coshan. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.63664" title="Icones Plantarum Asiaticarum. Part IV, Diccotyledonous Plants. Arranged by J. M'Clelland. Printed by A. B. Coshan." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.63664" year="1854">Griffith 1854</bibRefCitation>
), the single drawing cannot be considered as the holotype because the corresponding specimens that were collected and used by Griffith to prepare the description, although uncited, may still exist (see Art. 9 Ex. 2 of the ICN). Furthermore, fig. 2 of plate DCIV (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.63664" author="Griffith, W" journalOrPublisher="Bellamy, Calcutta" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B10" refString="Griffith, W, 1854. Icones Plantarum Asiaticarum. Part IV, Diccotyledonous Plants. Arranged by J. M'Clelland. Printed by A.B. Coshan. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.63664" title="Icones Plantarum Asiaticarum. Part IV, Diccotyledonous Plants. Arranged by J. M'Clelland. Printed by A. B. Coshan." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.63664" year="1854">Griffith 1854</bibRefCitation>
) is a poor drawing of leaves and flowers, which can hardly illustrate the key features of the taxon and is, therefore, unsuitable to serve as the lectotype. The specimens of potential original material collected by Griffith in Khasya Hills were found at BM, K and TCD. Unfortunately, none of the specimens bears the name &quot; 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. symplocifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="symplocifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">C. symplocifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; or the catalogue number. Considering the name was published in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Griffith’s">Griffith's</normalizedToken>
posthumous papers, it would be unsurprising that the original material of the name had not been clearly labelled. Based on the protologue and the drawing, one of the specimens, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Griffith s.n.</emphasis>
(TCD0018254; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Lectotype of Camellia symplocifolia Griff. (Griffith s. n., TCD 0018254). The red arrow indicates one position of the androecium and gynoecium. Image scanned by Ms J. Stone (TCD) and adapted by D. W. Zhao." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.84699.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702560" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">2</figureCitation>
), with flower materials (e.g. flower buds, androecia and gynoecia) and barcoded, is selected above as the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. symplocifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="symplocifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">C. symplocifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, the specimen (TCD0018254; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Lectotype of Camellia symplocifolia Griff. (Griffith s. n., TCD 0018254). The red arrow indicates one position of the androecium and gynoecium. Image scanned by Ms J. Stone (TCD) and adapted by D. W. Zhao." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.84699.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702560" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">2</figureCitation>
) can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. caudata" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">C. caudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wall. that was listed on the same page of 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.70351" author="Griffith, W" journalOrPublisher="Bellamy, Calcutta" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B9" refString="Griffith, W, 1848. Itinerary Notes of Plants Collected in the Khasyah and Bootan Mountains, 1837-38, in Affghanisthan and Neighbouring Countries, 1839 to 1841. Arranged by J. M'Clelland. Printed by Mr. J.F. Bellamy, Calcutta, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.70351" title="Itinerary Notes of Plants Collected in the Khasyah and Bootan Mountains, 1837 - 38, in Affghanisthan and Neighbouring Countries, 1839 to 1841. Arranged by J. M'Clelland. Printed by Mr. J. F." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.70351" year="1848">Griffith (1848)</bibRefCitation>
by its subsessile flower buds and glabrous filaments, whereas the latter bears pedicellate flower buds and hairy filaments.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.84699.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702560" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Figure 2.</emphasis>
Lectotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="Camellia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Camellia symplocifolia" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="symplocifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Camellia symplocifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Griff. (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Griffith s.n.</emphasis>
, TCD0018254). The red arrow indicates one position of the androecium and gynoecium. Image scanned by Ms J. Stone (TCD) and adapted by D.W. Zhao.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="Camellia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Camellia symplocifolia" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="symplocifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Camellia symplocifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is treated as a heterotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. kissi" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="kissi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">C. kissi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wall. by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sealy, JR" journalOrPublisher="The Royal Horticultural Society, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B15" refString="Sealy, JR, 1958. A Revision of the Genus Camellia. The Royal Horticultural Society, London" title="A Revision of the Genus Camellia." year="1958">Sealy (1958</bibRefCitation>
: 197), 
<bibRefCitation author="Chang, HT" journalOrPublisher="The Editorial Staff of the Journal of Sun Yatsen University, Guangzhou" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B2" refString="Chang, HT, 1981. A Taxonomy of the Genus Camellia. The Editorial Staff of the Journal of Sun Yatsen University, Guangzhou" title="A Taxonomy of the Genus Camellia." year="1981">Chang (1981</bibRefCitation>
: 35) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ming, TL" journalOrPublisher="Yunnan Science and Technology Press, Kunming" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B13" refString="Ming, TL, 2000. Monograph of the Genus Camellia. Yunnan Science and Technology Press, Kunming" title="Monograph of the Genus Camellia." year="2000">Ming (2000</bibRefCitation>
: 303). I agree with this treatment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
